feat: implement module dependency modification for dual-mode compatibility
- Add conditional import manager for safe WebUI module access - Modify core modules (setting.py, util.py) to use compatibility layer - Update all action modules to support dual-mode operation - Implement PNG info processing with fallback mechanisms - Add parameter copy-paste compatibility for WebUI/standalone modes - Create module initialization system for compatibility layer setup - Add comprehensive test suite for module compatibility - Maintain 100% backwards compatibility with AUTOMATIC1111 WebUI - Enable graceful degradation in standalone mode
This implements Backlog 005 - the most critical phase of dual-mode support, removing hard dependencies on WebUI modules while preserving full functionality.
Fixes: Module dependency abstraction Implements: Dual-mode module compatibility Tests: Module compatibility and integration tests Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: implement standalone entry point for independent execution
- Add main.py with CivitaiShortcutApp class for standalone mode - Implement comprehensive command-line interface with host/port/debug options - Create ui_adapter.py for standalone UI component integration - Add cross-platform startup scripts (start.sh, start.bat) - Include requirements.txt with core dependencies - Create default configuration system with JSON config files - Add comprehensive test suite for main app, CLI, and UI adapter - Include README_STANDALONE.md with complete usage documentation - Ensure compatibility layer integration for existing modules - Support graceful application lifecycle with signal handling
This enables Civitai Shortcut to run independently without AUTOMATIC1111 WebUI, providing users with a standalone web interface for model management and prompt recipe functionality.
Implements: Backlog 004 - 獨立執行入口與主程式建立 Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: align sampler provider with AUTOMATIC1111 implementation
- Update WebUISamplerProvider to use visible_samplers() function - Overhaul StandaloneSamplerProvider to match AUTOMATIC1111 behavior - Add scheduler combination support (e.g., 'DPM++ 2M Karras') - Implement case-insensitive alias resolution - Add 'dpmpp_2m_karras' alias for compatibility - Ensure consistent img2img sampler behavior - All 62 tests now pass (was 3 failing)

docs(README.zh-TW): clarify direct audio decoding and refine notes
- Revise the audio feature to highlight direct decoding and VAD-based synchronization without intermediate transcoding, and refine the wording of the time-axis correction and cache-management bullets for clarity.

feat: enable nextest profiles for coverage runs

ci: enable configurable test profiles in CI workflow
- Update CI workflow to invoke the quality_check script with `-p ci` instead of the hardcoded default profile - Add a `-p, --profile` option to scripts/quality_check.sh for selecting nextest profiles (default, ci, quick) with validation - Print the chosen nextest profile at script startup for clarity - Replace hardcoded `--profile default` flags in unit and integration test steps with the user-selected profile variable
